OL,3,C'We are not Eton': The private faith
OL,4,Cschools facing closure over VAT changes
OL,6,FThe average yearly fee to attend a
OL,7,Fprivate Islamic faith school in the
OL,8,Fcountry is #3000. Indeed, that is
OL,9,Fsignificantly less than some of the
OL,10,Fnation's most elite private schools.
OL,11,FEton College - which has a reputation
OL,12,Ffor producing Prime Ministers and
OL,13,Fworld leaders - charges up to #52,749
OL,14,Fas a yearly fee.
OL,16,FAnd yet, Darul Hadis Latifiah and Eton
OL,17,Fwill be expected to pay the same level
OL,18,Fof value-added tax with the Labour
OL,19,Fgovernment's reforms.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/14
