OL,3,C'We are not Eton': The private faith
OL,4,Cschools facing closure over VAT changes
OL,6,FThey also say the average yearly cost
OL,7,Ffor the taxpayer to educate one pupil
OL,8,Fis around #7,690, arguing even if a
OL,9,Fsmall percentage of the 54,000 pupils
OL,10,Faffected by the new VAT rules, were to
OL,11,Fmove to state schools, the additional
OL,12,Fcost to the government could wipe out
OL,13,Fany financial gain.
OL,15,FJulie Robinson, Chief Executive of
OL,16,FIndependent Schools Council says she
OL,17,Fis worried about the loss of diversity
OL,18,Fin education that the VAT policy could
OL,19,Fcause.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/14
